      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 4 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Built on Yesterday."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The Convention let five Founding Fathers debate a single topic in one round of monologues. The Founders' Court runs two rounds — opening statements, then rebuttals where each founder reads all four opponents and attacks the strongest opposing claim by name — and then a third AI takes the bench: Chief Justice John Marshall reads the full transcript and rules on who argued best."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com/p/summer-into-ai-week2-submission-zezek",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Eric's Zezek the Goblin (Week 2)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " gave one AI character a persistent personality (a web-based goblin brain). Founders' Court runs five personality-anchored characters simultaneously and makes them fight — then adds a sixth AI whose only job is to judge the other five"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Built on yesterday — what changed"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ],
          "text": "The original: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://jakestrait5.substack.com/p/summer-into-ai-2026-the-convention",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "The Convention (Week 2)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — five founders each gave one speech on a topic, in sequence"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Two debate rounds — after opening statements, each founder reads all four opponents and rebuts the strongest claim by name"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A third AI role: Chief Justice Marshall reads the full transcript and delivers a structured judicial opinion on who argued best — the winner is crowned gold"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Extended thinking streams live in a collapsible Reasoning panel per founder"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Six contrasting ElevenLabs voices with auto-speak — founders voice their opening lines in sequence, and Chief Justice Marshall announces the final ruling aloud"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Round 1 — parallel extended thinking streams"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — all five founders stream simultaneously via SSE. Each column shows a collapsible Reasoning panel with live thinking tokens, so you watch Washington deliberate before he speaks. Each system prompt is anchored with three real quotes from that founder's writings."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Round 2 — targeted rebuttals"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — after all five finish, the frontend collects all five arguments and fires a second round of parallel streams. Each founder receives the other four arguments, picks the strongest opposing claim, and dismantles it by name. \"Hamilton's assertion that commerce requires...\" — that kind of specific."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "The Chief Justice — AI judging AI"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — when the rebuttals end, a new endpoint sends the full two-round transcript to Claude playing Chief Justice John Marshall. A forced tool call returns a structured opinion: the best advocate, why they won on argumentation quality, and a 2-3 paragraph judicial opinion in period voice. The winner's column is crowned gold. Three distinct AI roles: generate, rebut, judge."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Six distinct ElevenLabs voices"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — each founder auto-speaks their opening lines as they finish (Franklin is an old sage, Hamilton a young firebrand), and when the court adjourns, Chief Justice Marshall announces his ruling aloud from the bench. Click Speak on any founder for their full argument."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Pick one of six modern constitutional controversies — AI rights, digital surveillance, executive power, and more."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Watch all five founders stream their opening arguments simultaneously. Click any Reasoning panel to expand the extended thinking."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "After round 1 completes, the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Rebuttal Round"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " opens automatically in the courtroom transcript — each founder attacks the strongest opposing claim by name."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "When the court adjourns, "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Chief Justice Marshall"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " deliberates and rules on who argued best — watch for the gold crown on the winning founder's column."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
